        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 9 at 4:15PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 414 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles east of Hartford to 8 miles west of
Decatur to near Dowagiac. Movement was northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kalamazoo...           Portage...             Paw Paw...
Hartford...            Mattawan...            Lawton...
Decatur...             Schoolcraft...         Westwood...
Alamo...               Keeler...              Lawrence...
Oshtemo...             Glendale...            Kendall...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for
southwestern Michigan.</instruction>
